summary:
I inspected the cluster leader-election code and found the quorum check in `app/cluster/node.go` was wrong. The code allowed a candidate to become leader with “half or more” of the votes using integer division (`finalVotes >= totalNodes/2`), so in a 5-node cluster each partition of size two could elect its own leader after a network split. I changed the code to require a strict majority:

```go
// Check if we have enough votes for a quorum
majority := totalNodes/2 + 1
if finalVotes >= majority {
    ...
}
```

This ensures only partitions containing more than half of the nodes can elect a leader. I also rebuilt the binary via `test.sh` and reran the provided script—both the single simulation and the repeated safety checks now report only a single leader being elected.
